SYNOPSIS
========
   mixed query_notify_fail(        )
   mixed query_notify_fail(intÂ flag)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   If flag(E) is not given or 0: return the string or closure which was last 
   set as error message for this command (with notify_fail(E)).

   If flag(E) is given and 1: return the object which issued the last 
   notify_fail(E).

   If nothing was set yet, return 0.

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.2.7)
   - changed (3.2.8) -- added the flag(E) parameter.

SEE ALSO
========
   add_action(E), query_verb(E), query_command(E), notify_fail(E), hook(H)
